data.name: Kafrit Group
data.description:
Founded in 1973, Kafrit Industries (1993) Ltd strives to create better and optimized solutions for the Plastic Industry. Kafrit Masterbatches and Compounds technologies have always been designed with great care to support and empower our customer’s products.
We promise to be an open and responsive to customer’s needs, providing the widest range of quality products and tailor- made solutions.
We seek to make our product more sustainable and to positively impact in all aspects the communities where we work and live.

data.name: KAFRIT SAB 0C430 EVA
data.description: KAFRIT SAB 0C430 EVA functions as a slip and anti-blocking agent specifically designed for compatible films in the rubber industry. It's ideal for processing in banburys or kneaders. This formulation aligns with ethylene vinyl acetate (eva) polymers and resins, and the carrier includes polyethylenes (PE), resin-based, and ethylene vinyl acetate (eva).

data.name: CONSTAB SAB 06509 LD

summary.name: Synonyms
items: cis-13-Docosenamide, Erucamide, Erucic acid amide, Erucic amide, Erucoyl amide, Erucyl amide

data.description: CONSTAB SAB 06509 LD features a product composed of 5% highly purified erucamide slip additive and 5% synthetic silica. This formulation serves as both an anti-blocking agent and a slip agent, catering to the packaging sector, including food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT SL 0A864 LD
data.description: KAFRIT SL 0A864 LD presents a hot slip masterbatch product that's tailored for low coefficient of friction (COF) properties at elevated temperatures. Carried by polyethylenes (PE) and resins, this slip agent product is beneficial for packaging applications, including food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: CONSTAB AT 04673 LD
data.description: CONSTAB AT 04673 LD is an amine-free product offering short- and long-term antistatic effects at low humidity levels. It functions as an anti-static agent and is used in building and construction, electrical and electronics, printing, and packaging applications.

data.name: CONSTAB SAB 06569 LD
data.description: CONSTAB SAB 06569 LD is a synergistic combination of additives that provides balanced antiblocking and fast slip properties when processing mlld-pe, plastomers, or pe-copolymers; avoids screw slip and blooming; and provides excellent printing and sealing properties in comparison to oleamide or erucamide.

data.name: KAFRIT SAB 0656A EVA
data.description: KAFRIT SAB 0656A EVA is a slip antiblock combi-masterbatch that acts as an antistick in extruded, blown, and cast films. Prevents the sticking of films to hot surfaces and prevents the fusion of Eva shrink hoods. Suitable for films with high va-content.

data.name: KAFRIT SL 00T52 LD
data.description: KAFRIT SL 00T52 LD introduces a long-lasting slip agent that maintains good slip properties during storage in multilayered films. With high slip attributes, it serves the printing and packaging markets, particularly in packaging applications such as food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: CONSTAB AT 07560 LD
data.description: CONSTAB AT 07560 LD is an amine-free product that provides short- and long-term antistatic effects at low humidity levels. It functions as an anti-static agent and is suitable for electrical and electronic equipment, printing, and packaging, as well as applications in food and beverage packaging, industrial and transport packaging, and housings and enclosures.

data.name: CONSTAB AT 04131 LD
data.description: CONSTAB AT 04131 LD is an amine-free product designed for short- and long-term antistatic effects, even at very low humidity levels. These anti-static agents are carried by polyethylenes (PE) and resin-based materials, and they target the electrical and electronics markets as well as the printing and packaging markets.

With high slip attributes, it serves the printing and packaging markets, particularly in packaging applications such as food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT SL 0C600 LD
data.description: KAFRIT SL 0C600 LD introduces a distinctive slip agent thoughtfully formulated for medium- to long-term effects. Tailored for processes including blow molding and injection molding, its versatility positions it as a key player in the realms of printing and packaging. Its functional carrier comprises both a resin-based structure and polyethylene (PE).

data.name: KAFRIT AT 00U11 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AT 00U11 LD is an amine-free product designed for short- and long-term antistatic effects, even at very low humidity levels. These anti-static agents are carried by polyethylenes (PE) and resin-based materials, and they target the electrical and electronics markets as well as the printing and packaging markets.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 00T14C LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 00T14C LD serves as an antifog agent designed for cold fog applications. It's particularly applicable in laminated multi-layer barrier films and is well-suited for the double bubble process. This formulation, carried by polyethylene (PE) with a resin-based foundation, finds its place in the printing and packaging industries, specifically in food and beverage packaging. It also caters to the needs of plastics and elastomers, particularly in film, food packaging, and lamination film.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 00S03 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 00S03 LD is an anti-fogging agent product that uses polyethylene (PE) as its carrier. It features good weather stability and is suitable for a wide range of climatic conditions, providing long-lasting antifog properties. It is used in greenhouse and tunnel films for the agriculture and feed markets.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 00P52A EVA
data.description: KAFRIT AF 00P52A EVA presents a transparent antifog masterbatch specifically designed for double roof and solarization films in the agriculture and feed markets. KAFRIT AF 00P52A EVA offers excellent transparency properties for use in agricultural films like greenhouse and tunnel films.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 002521 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 002521 LD is designed for cold- and hot-fog applications. This antifog masterbatch is highly effective in preventing fogging. It serves as an anti-fogging agent and is suitable for polyethylene (PE) and resin-based materials. This product finds its place in the printing and packaging markets, including food and beverage packaging and plastics and elastomers applications.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 15800 LD
data.description: KAFRIT CB 15800 LD is a product combining white and UV masterbatch functions. It acts as a UV protector and pigment and is colored white. This product belongs to the color masterbatches, additive masterbatches, antioxidants and stabilizers, and pigments and colorants families. Its applications include silage and stretch films and are used in the agriculture and feed markets.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 60H06 LL BLUE & MAGNET & UV
data.description: KAFRIT CB 60H06 LL BLUE & MAGNET & UV combines magnet colors with UV protection in a custom blue color. It serves as a UV protector and pigment and is compatible with polyethylenes (PE) and resin-based carriers, applicable in blow molding and injection molding.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 70H06 LL
data.description: KAFRIT CB 70H06 LL is a UV protector product that combines a dark green color and UV masterbatch. It belongs to various product families, such as additive masterbatches, color masterbatches, antioxidants and stabilizers, and pigments and colorants. It is used in the agriculture and feed markets.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 00T46A LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 00T46A LD is a unique anti-fogging agent that is suitable for polyamide films in both hot and cold applications. It's compatible with polyamides and polyethylenes (PE) in the printing and packaging market, with applications like food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 00S98 LD
data.description: KAFRIT CB 00S98 LD introduces a combi-batch product designed for shrink-hood applications over PE bags. This formulation of KAFRIT CB 00S98 LD combines anti-blocking agent, anti-tack agent, and UV absorber functionalities. It serves the printing and packaging industries and provides versatility in applications.

data.name: KAFRIT AB 0U470 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AB 0U470 LD is an anti-blocking agent product with a polyethylene (PE) carrier. It is non-phenolic and contains 70% purified silica that is crystalline-free and phenol-free. This product is used in the printing and packaging market for applications in food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT AT 0B790 LL
data.description: KAFRIT AT 0B790 LL offers a synergistic blend of fast and slow migrating products that yield a swift start-up and a long-lasting antistatic effect. Operating as an anti-static agent, it seamlessly accommodates blow molding and injection molding techniques. The formulation employs polyethylene (PE) as the carrier within a resin-based framework. This versatile formulation caters to consumer goods and the printing and packaging sectors.

data.name: KAFRIT CC 60440 LD BLUE
data.description: KAFRIT CC 60440 LD BLUE is a blue pigment with photo-selective properties. It functions as a pigment, providing a blue color to the material. The product is designed to be photo-selective, meaning it filters and absorbs specific wavelengths of light, which helps prevent botrytis sporulation. Botrytis is a type of fungus that causes gray mold in plants, and by being photo-selective, this blue pigment can aid in controlling its growth and reducing its impact on plants.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 0B680 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 0B680 LD is an anti-fogging agent product featuring a polyethylene (PE) carrier. With its commendable weather stability, it is particularly well-suited for use in hot climate conditions. This product delivers a moderate, long-lasting anti-fog effect. It is categorized within the product families of additive masterbatches and surface modifiers.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 0F140 LD Diffuser and UV
data.description: KAFRIT CB 0F140 LD Diffuser and UV is a product that contains Ni quencher for excellent chemical stability. It offers an anti-virus effect and blocks UV radiation up to 380 nm. It also contains thermal irradiation. The carrier used is polyethylene (PE). This masterbatch belongs to the product families of additive masterbatches, antioxidants and stabilizers, and processing aids.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 10470 LD
data.description: KAFRIT CB 10470 LD is a product combining UV protection and pigment functions. It is colored white and belongs to the color masterbatches, additive masterbatches, antioxidants and stabilizers, and pigments and colorants families. Its applications include silage and stretch films and are used in the agriculture and feed markets.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 14350 LD
data.description: KAFRIT CB 14350 LD is a product that functions as an anti-static agent and is a white pigment. It is combined with AT. This product belongs to the color masterbatches, pigments and colorants, and surface modifiers families and is used in the printing and packaging markets. Its applications include cast films, film, and food packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 0875A LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 0875A LD is an antimist masterbatch designed to prevent mist formation in poorly ventilated greenhouses. It's recommended for use alongside AF 03590 LD or AF 00s03 LD. The carrier used is polyethylene (PE). Its primary market is agriculture and feed.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 50H60 LD
data.description: KAFRIT CB 50H60 LD combines a deep pink color with UV protection and is particularly designed for agricultural applications such as agricultural films, silage covers, and stretch films. This product also supports breast cancer awareness campaigns. It falls under various product families, including additive masterbatches, color masterbatches, antioxidants and stabilizers, and pigments and colourants.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 90750 LL MIST GREY & UV & MAGNET
data.description: KAFRIT CB 90750 LL MIST GREY & UV & MAGNET combines magnet colors with UV protection. It serves as both a UV protector and pigment in custom gray colors. It belongs to the color masterbatches and additive masterbatches families and is applicable in markets like printing and packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 61880 LL BLUE
data.description: KAFRIT CB 61880 LL BLUE is a product that is designed for protective banana bags, enhancing fruit weight and quality. It functions as both a UV protector and pigment in blue color, targeting food and beverage packaging and plastics and elastomers applications in the printing and packaging markets.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 80C98 LL BEIGE & MAGNET & UV
data.description: KAFRIT CB 80C98 LL BEIGE & MAGNET & UV combines magnet colors with UV protection in a custom beige color. It serves as both a UV protector and pigment in the color masterbatches, additive masterbatches, and antioxidants and stabilizers product families.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 70J14 LL
data.description: KAFRIT CB 70J14 LL is a solid masterbatch specially formulated to offer a light green color along with effective UV protection. This versatile product serves a dual purpose as both a UV protector and a pigment, imparting a vibrant green hue to the material. It has gained significant traction in the agriculture & field market, finding applications in various types of agricultural films, including silage and stretch films.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 80987A
data.description: KAFRIT CB 80987A is a product that functions as a UV protector and pigment. It is compatible with polypropylene (PP) and is processed using blow molding and injection molding methods. The product is used in the printing and packaging markets, particularly for industrial and transport packaging applications. It belongs to the antioxidants, stabilizers and pigments and colorants product families.

data.name: KAFRIT CB 80C47 LL BROWN & MAGNET & UV
data.description: KAFRIT CB 80C47 LL BROWN & MAGNET & UV combines magnet colors with UV protection in a custom brown color. It functions as a UV protector and pigment and is suitable for plastic and elastomer processing methods like blow molding and injection molding.

data.name: KAFRIT AF 00V84 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AF 00V84 LD is an anti-fogging agent product that uses polyethylene (PE) as its carrier. KAFRIT AF 00V84 LD features excellent transparency properties and is a highly transparent antifog masterbatch used in greenhouse films for the agriculture and feed markets.

data.name: KAFRIT AB 0K630 LD
data.description: KAFRIT AB 0K630 LD is a product consisting of 70% purified silica that's free from crystalline content. It forms a highly concentrated anti-blocking masterbatch, effectively preventing film blockage on rolls. This formulation serves as an anti-blocking agent and is carried by polyethylene (PE) within a resin-based structure. The product caters to the printing and packaging sectors, finding applications in food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT CC 21930 LL
data.description: KAFRIT CC 21930 LL is a reflective silver pigment that functions as a pigment, imparting a silver color to the material. It serves as an insect repellent, deterring insects from settling on the treated surface. Additionally, the pigment helps reduce soil temperature by reflecting sunlight away from the soil.

data.name: KAFRIT CC 5A882 UNI RED
data.description: KAFRIT CC 5A882 UNI RED is a red pigment with photo-selective properties. It functions as a pigment, imparting a red color to the material. The product is specifically designed for use in monofilament and slit tape nets. It is photo-selective, meaning it can manipulate the red/far-red ratio of the spectrum, which influences plant morphology. By using this red pigment, it is possible to control certain aspects of plant growth and development through the manipulation of light conditions, promoting specific responses in the plants.

data.name: KAFRIT AB 0F210 LL
data.description: KAFRIT AB 0F210 LL is a high-quality pe-film product featuring 10% synthetic silica with a particle size of 4 µm. As an anti-blocking agent, it ensures consistent high quality for packaging applications in food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging.

data.name: KAFRIT AB 060126 PA
data.description: KAFRIT AB 060126 PA is a product that functions as an anti-blocking agent. It uses polyamides as its carrier and features good dispersion. The product is used in the printing and packaging market for food and beverage packaging and industrial and transport packaging applications. It belongs to the additive masterbatches and surface modifier product families.
